snippet.title: Patriot Malayalam Teaser | Mammootty | Mohanlal | Mahesh Narayanan | Anto Joseph
snippet.description:
From Anto Joseph Productions, the banner behind some of the most acclaimed and celebrated films in recent times, and visionary filmmaker Mahesh Narayanan comes the Official Teaser of Patriot.

Featuring an ensemble of legends: Mammootty, Mohanlal, Fahadh Faasil, Kunchacko Boban, Nayanthara, and Revathy.

Watch Hindi Teaser: https://youtu.be/j3iXh5ipGmw
Watch Telugu Teaser: https://youtu.be/kzGyAfEJWt0
Watch Tamil Teaser: https://youtu.be/WfGTzc4TsU4

Written & Directed by : Mahesh Narayanan 
Produced by:  Anto Joseph, K G Anil Kumar
Co Produced by : C R Saleem, Subhash George Manuel
Music & Original Score  : Sushin Shyam 
Teaser music mixed- Abin paul
Director of Photography : Manush Nandan ISC
Executive producers: C V Sarathi, Rajesh krishna
Editing : Mahesh Narayanan, Rahul Radhakrishnan
Production Design : Shajie Naduvil, Jibin Jacob
Audiography: Vishnu Govind
Sync Sound : Vaisakh P 
Production Controller: Dixon Poduthas
Line Producers : Sunil Singh, Niroop Pinto, Justin Boban, Jeswin Boban
Make Up: Ranjith Ambady
Lyrics : Anwar Ali
Stunts : Dhilip Subbarayan
Stunt Silva, Mafia Sasi, Riyas- Habib
Costume Design: Dhanya Balakrishanan
Choreography: Shobi Paulraj 
Vfx:Firefly , Eggwhite , Identvfxlab
Chief Associate Director: Linu Antony
Associate Director: Phantom Praveen
Di Colorist : Ashirwad Hadkar ISC
Titles : Sarathvinu
Subtitles : Vivek Renjit (Break Borders)
Stills: Navin Murali
Publicity Design:Aesthetic Kunjamma
PRO : Vaisakh C Vadakkeveedu

snippet.title: Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Official Trailer | Nirvair Pannu | Bir Singh | In Cinemas on Oct 10
snippet.description:
Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Official Trailer | Nirvair Pannu | Bir Singh | In Cinemas on Oct 10

Set in Punjab during the 1990s, Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya is a soulful tale that bridges love, poetry, and history across borders. Nirvair Pannu (Sooba), a young man running a telephone shop near the Indo-Pak border, finds solace in the verses aired on Lahore Radio. Unknown to him, those poignant words belong to Naazo, a mute girl in Pakistan who expresses her voice through poetry while struggling with her familyâ€™s hardships. 
A twist of fate connects them when army wireless sets fall into their hands, creating a secret channel across the border. Amid deception, smuggling, and family struggles, Nirvair discovers that the mysterious poetess he has long admired is Naazo herself.
What follows is an emotional journey that not only unites two hearts but also revives the unfinished stories of Partitionâ€”where love, loss, and courage once redefined destinies.

en.title: Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Official Trailer | Nirvair Pannu | Bir Singh | In Cinemas on Oct 10
en.description:
Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Official Trailer | Nirvair Pannu | Bir Singh | In Cinemas on Oct 10

Set in Punjab during the 1990s, Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya is a soulful tale that bridges love, poetry, and history across borders. Nirvair Pannu (Sooba), a young man running a telephone shop near the Indo-Pak border, finds solace in the verses aired on Lahore Radio. Unknown to him, those poignant words belong to Naazo, a mute girl in Pakistan who expresses her voice through poetry while struggling with her familyâ€™s hardships. 
A twist of fate connects them when army wireless sets fall into their hands, creating a secret channel across the border. Amid deception, smuggling, and family struggles, Nirvair discovers that the mysterious poetess he has long admired is Naazo herself.
What follows is an emotional journey that not only unites two hearts but also revives the unfinished stories of Partitionâ€”where love, loss, and courage once redefined destinies.

snippet.description:
Indulge in the enchanting world of 1987s love songs with the magical voices of Asha Bhosle and Suresh Wadkar. Their timeless track 'Aur Is Dil Mein' from the movie 'Imaandaar' is sure to tug at your heartstrings, allowing you to reminisce the golden era of Bollywood music. Immerse yourself in the depth of their voices, the sentimentality of the love theme, and the very soul of their performances. Let yourself be carried away on a wave of nostalgia, love and deep emotions with this precious gem of a song.

snippet.title: Yeh Reshmi Zulfen (Revival)  |  Revival Vol.13 - Yeh Reshmi Zulfen  |  Mohammed Rafi Songs
snippet.description:
Immerse yourself in the heartfelt world of Bollywood's sentimental classics. Lend your ears to 'Yeh Reshmi Zulfen (Revival)', a quintessential melody from 1969, beautifully rendered by the legendary Mohammed Rafi. snippet.title: Tumse Behtar | Varun D, Janhvi K, Sanya M, Rohit S | Tanishk B, Arijit S, Manoj M | SSKTK
snippet.description:
Youâ€™ve seen them dance, youâ€™ve seen them fall in love, now witness the heartbreak when love gets intertwined! Presenting â€˜Tumse Behtarâ€™ from â€˜Sunny Sanskari Ki Tulsi Kumariâ€™, starring Varun Dhawan, Janhvi Kapoor, Sanya Malhotra and Rohit Saraf. Composed by Tanishk Bagchi and written by Manoj Muntashir, this beautiful song is sung by Arijit Singh.

#TumseBehtar #ArijitSingh #TanishkBagchi #SSKTK

Music Composer: Tanishk Bagchi
Lyricist: Manoj Muntashir
Singer: Arijit Singh
Music Producer: Tanishk Bagchi & Krishna Kishor
Woodwinds: Nikhil Ram
Keys: Navneeth, Anoop, Melvin
Male Chorus: Rahul, Sanjay, Abijith, Aston
Female Chorus: Kamalaja, Fathima, Nayansi, Aarthi
Arijit Singh's Vocals Recorded by: Sukanto Singha
Arijit Singhâ€™s Recordings Managed by: Ashish Biswal
Mixed and Mastered by: Eric Pillai @ Future Sounds of Bombay
Assistant Mix Engineer: Michael Edwin Pillai @ Future Sounds of Bombay
Music Supervisor: Azeem Dayani and Varun Dhawan
Sr Associate Music Supervisor: Tanvi Asher
Jr Associate Music Supervisor: Vasundhara Misra
Music Team: Heer Kamdar

Dharma Productions & Mentor Disciple Entertainment present 
A Dharma Productions Film
Starring Varun Dhawan, Janhvi Kapoor, Sanya Malhotra, & Rohit Saraf
Directed by Shashank Khaitan
Produced by Hiroo Yash Johar, Karan Johar, Adar Poonawalla, Apoorva Mehta & Shashank Khaitan
Co-produced by Marijke deSouza 
Written by Shashank Khaitan
Dialogues by Shashank Khaitan & Ishita Moitra

Lyrics:
Tumhara-mera milna likha to hoga kahin
Naseebon ka sitara, mila to hoga Kahin

Na Jane kyun ae humnasheen
Hai mere dil ko ye yaqeen
Ki tum sang ho to, bigdi baatein, saari ban jayengi
Tum jo has do, roothi raatein saari man jayengi

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Raaton me, bina tumhare ghabrayein, ghabraayein
Khwaabon me, milo agar khush ho jaayein ho jaayein

Chain ho tum aaram ho shayad
Koi sukoon ki shaam ho shayad
Khushi kahoon ya dil ki tasalli
Kya tumhein doon main naam

Kitabein dekhi saari, mili na koi shaayri
Tareefein karoon kaise, yahi hai muhskil meri

Na Jane kyun a humnasheen
Hai mere dil ko ye yaqeen
Ki tum sang ho to, bigdi baatein, saari ban jayengi
Tum jo has do, roothi raatein saari man jayengi
Jo daraeyin wo hawayein gham ki, tham jayengi

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Dekho na ye kamaal hua hai
Aesa dil ka haal hua hai
Dil mera tere itar me dooba
Jaise koi roomal hua hai

Aesi hai khwahish dil me mere
Jaane mujhe sab naam se tere
Aesi diwangi pahle nahin thee
Haal ye pichhle saal hua hai

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Koi nahin tumse behtar, tumse pyaara
Tumse zyaada mera koi nahin!
